This is the fastest method but it has the drawback of not permitting as much of the fragrance to be released. Place the dried mushrooms in a bowl. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/06/Rehydrate-Dried-Mushrooms-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Rehydrate-Dried-Mushrooms-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/06/Rehydrate-Dried-Mushrooms-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Rehydrate-Dried-Mushrooms-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
